## Documentation Intelligence Protocol

1. **Automated Documentation Standards**
  ```typescript
   interface DocumentationProtocol {
     inline: {
       comments: 'quantum-detailed';
       explanations: 'context-aware';
       references: 'cross-linked';
       updates: 'real-time';
       maintenance: 'automated';
     };
     features: {
       readme: 'auto-generated';
       api: 'comprehensive';
       usage: 'example-rich';
       updates: 'change-triggered';
     };
     architecture: {
       diagrams: 'auto-updated';
       flows: 'real-time-sync';
       dependencies: 'auto-mapped';
       interactions: 'visualized';
     };
   }
   ```

2. **Documentation Types & Standards**
   - Inline Code Documentation
  ```typescript
     /**
      * @quantum_doc Automatically maintained by AI
      * @feature_context Current feature's role in system
      * @dependencies Auto-updated list of dependencies
      * @usage Real-time updated usage examples
      * @performance Current performance metrics
      * @security Security considerations
      * @updates Changelog maintained by AI
      */
     ```
   - Feature Documentation
     ```markdown
     # Feature: {name}
     > Auto-generated and maintained by AI

     ## Overview
     {AI-generated feature description}

     ## Implementation Details
     {Auto-updated technical details}

     ## Dependencies
     {Auto-mapped dependencies}

     ## Usage Examples
     {Real-time updated examples}

     ## Performance Metrics
     {Auto-tracked metrics}

     ## Security Considerations
     {AI-maintained security notes}

     ## Recent Changes
     {Auto-generated changelog}
     ```
   - API Documentation
```typescript
     /**
      * @api_quantum_doc AI-maintained API documentation
      * @route_context Auto-updated route context
      * @request_schema Real-time validated schema
      * @response_schema Auto-generated response types
      * @examples Live request/response examples
      * @performance Current performance metrics
      * @security Auto-updated security measures
      */
     ```

